docs.snippet: BENUMBED by the loss of Wiley Post, one of the world's great pilots, and of Will Rogers, air transport's No. 1 passenger, who had traveled some 300,000 miles on scheduled airlines without injury, the aviation industry still was able to function with...
docs.lead_paragraph: BENUMBED by the loss of Wiley Post, one of the world's great pilots, and of Will Rogers, air transport's No. 1 passenger, who had traveled some 300,000 miles on scheduled airlines without injury, the aviation industry still was able to function with impressive speed and smoothness in the sad mission of flying the bodies of the two victims of their pioneering vacation jaunt to the scene of their funeral rites last week.

docs.snippet: Foreign exchanges declined last week. Particular weakness was evident on Saturday when the largest share of the losses on the week were registered. Traders were loath to attribute the reaction to the reported deeding of exploitation rights in...
docs.lead_paragraph: Foreign exchanges declined last week. Particular weakness was evident on Saturday when the largest share of the losses on the week were registered. Traders were loath to attribute the reaction to the reported deeding of exploitation rights in Ethiopia to Standard Oil interests as the cause, but it was noticeable that with lower cables from abroad on Saturday morning, coupled with absence of demand on this side, the decline made easy progress.

docs.snippet: WASHINGTON, Sept. 5. -- Russian purchases of American un-manufactured cotton worth $3,559,469 and of heavy machinery valued at $1,156,632 carried July exports to that country from the United States to more than double the value of those of the...
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Sept. 5. -- Russian purchases of American un-manufactured cotton worth $3,559,469 and of heavy machinery valued at $1,156,632 carried July exports to that country from the United States to more than double the value of those of the preceding month and quadrupled those of the corresponding month last year, according to figures made public today by the Commerce Department.
